# CardShield Project Rules
- Always use 'async/await' for database (SQLAlchemy AsyncSession) and Redis (redis-py async).
- Use SQLModel for shared Pydantic/SQLAlchemy definitions to reduce boilerplate.
- For "Velocity" features, prioritize Redis Sorted Sets (ZSET) over PostgreSQL queries.
- Follow a Service-Pattern: Keep API endpoints thin; put scoring logic in `app/services/`.
- Ensure all PostgreSQL queries use indexed columns (user_id, timestamp).